  "texts": [
    "Mimicking human cognitive functions, neural networks, and in particular specialized forms like CNNs, excel in pattern recognition and decision-making in numerous applications, including image analysis.",
    "The availability of extensive training datasets is crucial for DL, as they provide detailed information necessary for models to learn effectively and generalize to unseen scenarios.",
    "Data preprocessing-a vital phase in the DL workflow-uses these data encompasses cleaning, normalizing, and transforming raw data into a format compatible with neural networks, ensuring consistency and stability during network training.",
    "For microfossil image analysis, CNNs, transfer learning (TL), Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) Transformers and hybrid models have emerged as key DL techniques.",
    "CNNs, with their exceptional image processing capabilities, are well-suited for analyzing the intricate patterns in microfossil imagery."
